The minister of foreign affairs, Geoffrey Onyeama has tested positive for COVID-19. Onyeama disclosed this via his twitter handle on Sunday and also said that he was going into isolation in a health facility, . He said he had previously done the COVID-19 test three times and that the three results were all negative while this fourth one just returned positive. “Did my fourth Covid-19 test yesterday at the first sign of a throat irritation and unfortunately this time it came back positive. That is life! Win some lose some. Heading for isolation in a health facility and praying for the best,” Onyeama said. The NCDC update on Saturday shows that the number of the Coronavirus Disease in Nigeria now stands at 36,107, with 14,938 patients discharged and 778 deaths recorded. At least 28 of Nigeria’s 36 states reported new cases of COVID-19 adding up to 653 new infections according to the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC). The NCDC update on Saturday shows that the number of the coronavirus Disease in Nigeria now stands at 36,107, with 14,938 patients discharged and 778 deaths recorded. Lagos State recorded the highest number of new infections with 115  followed by Kwara State with 85 cases. Enugu State reported 80 new cases, the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) had 78, Rivers State had 36, Ondo State had 35, Oyo had 30, Katsina State had 28, while Kaduna and Abia states had 19 each. Nasarawa State reported 18 new cases, Plateau State had 17, Imo State had 16, while Ogun, Ebonyi, Benue and Kano states all had nine cases each. In Delta State, there were eight new cases, seven in Bauchi State, six in Ekiti State, four each in Gombe, Bayelsa, Adamawa and Osun states. Cross River, Yobe, Borno and Zamfara states had had single case each.